{
  "texts": [
    "With similar ambitions, Song and Fan (2021) explicitly improves pose detection methods by using different modules from the VGG11 network for different feature fusion methods.",
    "To accomplish this, estimates of features are sampled from the VGG11 network and local features of points are first aggregated.",
    "After the image passes through a semantic segmentation network, a segmented target (i.e.",
    "a body part) is passed into the feature fusion network.",
    "This splices and fuses the RGB features of the segmented image, local point-cloud features and global view features to form a final feature vector which is then reduced to a scalar value for classifying the body part."
  ]
}